#: ../../source/user_guide/forms.rst:206 d942f6516f0f45318a4cf937c39a2147
msgid "Sparsity: what the assembled output actually looks like"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/user_guide/forms.rst:208 0bff7a83f9ef4630bf536b68e011d0a3
msgid ""
"The :class:`~tensormesh.sparse.SparseMatrix` is COO-format on top of "
"``torch_sla.SparseTensor``; you can ``@`` against it, ``.solve(b)`` "
"against it, or densify it for inspection. The two panels below show the "
"sparsity pattern of the Laplace stiffness above, next to the 2D-"
"elasticity stiffness on the *same* mesh:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/user_guide/forms.rst:214 26d20ce4597a448d9d05fe78355ab140
msgid "Stiffness sparsity, scalar Laplace vs 2D elasticity"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/user_guide/forms.rst:218 81b39050c55540298e7c300c75e54352
msgid ""
"The scalar Laplace stiffness has one entry per ``(i, j)`` adjacent node "
"pair. The 2D-elasticity stiffness has the *same* connectivity but each "
"entry is now a :math:`2 \\times 2` block (one row/col per displacement "
"component), giving a matrix four times larger with sixteen times the non-"
"zeros. The library detects the block structure from the rank of your "
"``forward`` return — see the next section."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/user_guide/forms.rst:227 b185405ac81748a8940b481730c84189
msgid "Vector-valued forms and block-CSR output"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/user_guide/forms.rst:229 daabd712a8bc4132aff2ad81e449fc45
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"For vector-valued problems (linear elasticity, Stokes velocity blocks, "
"electromagnetics in vector form) each node carries :math:`H > 1` degrees "
"of freedom. The bilinear form integrand for an entry :math:`(i, j)` is "
"then a :math:`H \\times H` block, and the assembled matrix has shape "
":math:`[N_\\text{points}\\, H,\\, N_\\text{points}\\, H]`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/user_guide/forms.rst:235 36a8922981a24ba9af16292134b8a11c
msgid ""
"The library decides scalar vs block by inspecting the *rank* of what your"
" ``forward`` returns:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/user_guide/forms.rst:238 f4fe4a1277dd4f02bf34a3d7ec7b6fba
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"``forward`` returns a 2-D tensor ``[B, B]`` → scalar, output shape "
":math:`[N_\\text{points}, N_\\text{points}]`;"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/user_guide/forms.rst:240 2043c3e3fc084a12856d40de76284e2f
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"``forward`` returns a 4-D tensor ``[B, B, H, H]`` → block, output shape "
":math:`[N_\\text{points}\\, H, N_\\text{points}\\, H]`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/user_guide/forms.rst:243 63681a832e3540ce96991c01269db797
msgid "For linear elasticity in 2D, the integrand at a quadrature point is"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/user_guide/forms.rst:245 bed839b92b86460ba7dce9a7bc719c06
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"K_{ij}^{\\alpha\\beta} \\;=\\;\n"
"\\int_\\Omega \\mathbf{B}_i^T\\, \\mathbf{C}\\, \\mathbf{B}_j "
"\\,\\mathrm{d}\\Omega,\n"
"\\qquad\n"
"\\mathbf{B}_i \\;=\\; \\text{Voigt}(\\nabla \\phi_i),"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/user_guide/forms.rst:252 35fba722582347ccacde020518c1df5e
msgid ""
"which is exactly the built-in "
":class:`~tensormesh.LinearElasticityElementAssembler`:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/user_guide/forms.rst:269 daf0b390d56445e6ac6223c91af60778
msgid ""
"The whole 2D mesh of 143 nodes produces a :math:`286 \\times 286` "
"stiffness — see the right panel of the figure above. Everything you read "
"about scalar problems on this page applies unchanged to block problems; "
"only the matrix shape grows."
msgstr ""

