#: ../../source/user_guide/forms.rst:563 9e4791e7bcef4bebaf5884a1f3f4ae07
msgid "Energy-based assemblers (``element_energy`` + ``.energy()``)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/user_guide/forms.rst:565 a9481a6e9b164c2b90a13d0166c5fff1
msgid ""
"For nonlinear materials the most natural quantity to define is the "
"*strain energy density* :math:`\\Psi`, not the residual or stiffness:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/user_guide/forms.rst:568 de57c918f0fc4283b7bb3d3c96757d38
msgid ""
"\\Pi(\\mathbf{u}) \\;=\\; \\int_\\Omega \\Psi(\\nabla \\mathbf{u})\\, "
"\\mathrm{d}\\Omega,\n"
"\\qquad\n"
"\\mathbf{f}_\\text{int} \\;=\\; \\frac{\\partial \\Pi}{\\partial "
"\\mathbf{u}},\n"
"\\qquad\n"
"\\mathbf{K}_\\text{tan} \\;=\\; \\frac{\\partial^2 \\Pi}{\\partial "
"\\mathbf{u}^2}."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/user_guide/forms.rst:576 21035a85dc4141ac867654db98525954
msgid ""
":class:`~tensormesh.ElementAssembler` supports this pattern via a "
"parallel method, ``ElementAssembler.energy``, that integrates an "
"``element_energy`` override and returns a scalar :class:`torch.Tensor`. "
"Because the entire pipeline is differentiable, ``E.backward()`` populates"
" ``u.grad`` with the internal force vector, and "
":func:`torch.autograd.functional.hessian` (or a Krylov-friendly Hessian-"
"vector product) gives the tangent stiffness:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/user_guide/forms.rst:596 66e610a193db4ecea268f1477655c10b
msgid ""
"Use the matrix-based path (``__call__`` returning a ``SparseMatrix``) for"
" *linear* and *bilinear-symmetric* problems where you already have a "
"closed-form integrand; use the energy path for hyperelasticity, "
"plasticity, and any case where autograd through the constitutive law is "
"the cleanest expression of the physics."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/user_guide/forms.rst:604 b350145156c948c58af704907c08a252
msgid "A custom form: reaction-diffusion"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/user_guide/forms.rst:606 7f9085cfac2d422c8e6ad3d1f114b083
msgid "Combining stiffness and mass in one assembler:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/user_guide/forms.rst:608 d4d057f9d96449c49794280e51c682bf
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"a(u, v) \\;=\\; \\int_{\\Omega} \\nabla u \\cdot \\nabla v \\;+\\; "
"\\kappa \\, u v \\, \\mathrm{d}\\Omega"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/user_guide/forms.rst:612 04585816fcb646b4a1b96a280256d308
msgid "is just two terms inside ``forward``:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/user_guide/forms.rst:625 5c537a9b209449f5bfec53320ee7bd2b
msgid ""
"Argument order doesn't matter — the dispatch is by name. Mixing in "
"``point_data`` is just more parameters:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/user_guide/forms.rst:638 9561cf785d1840dfb176cf0b5a4b191d
msgid ""
"This generalises straightforwardly: anything you can write as one "
"algebraic expression in PyTorch can go inside ``forward``, as long as the"
" return shape obeys the contract in :ref:`forms-contract`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/user_guide/forms.rst:646 3e27c7978a7d4e4d8181fa0435686387
msgid "Memory batching with ``batch_size``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/user_guide/forms.rst:648 6061b3798b734883b6425549cb943085
msgid ""
"For very fine meshes or high-order elements, holding all per-element "
"quadrature tensors in memory at once may not fit. The assembler "
"``__call__`` accepts a ``batch_size`` argument that splits the "
"*quadrature* dimension into chunks and accumulates the contribution:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/user_guide/forms.rst:657 aef10a7758da4ac2ab8a6dfa3a92bce8
msgid ""
"This is a memory knob, not problem-level vectorisation; for the latter "
"see :doc:`batched_workflows`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/user_guide/forms.rst:660 00af6cbc8d9b493399195d90973353c3
msgid "How to disable batching:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/user_guide/forms.rst:662 eaef31b2d9b44fadb7c79568059c91f3
msgid ""
":class:`~tensormesh.ElementAssembler` — default ``batch_size=-1`` "
"processes all quadrature at once."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/user_guide/forms.rst:664 b7a972a4b4374db1a20df5b09f7d57ab
msgid ""
":class:`~tensormesh.NodeAssembler` — default ``batch_size=1`` processes "
"one quadrature point at a time; pass ``-1`` or ``None`` to disable "
"batching and process all quadrature points at once."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/user_guide/forms.rst:667 b0e54794c38647fcac0c855cdcd43333
msgid ""
":class:`~tensormesh.FacetAssembler` — does not expose ``batch_size``; "
"facet integrals are small enough that batching has not been needed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/user_guide/forms.rst:670 05a3ffae2d4e4c0090ae9175c0ffed27
msgid ""
"Any positive integer ``batch_size`` produces the same assembled result as"
" the un-batched call. When ``batch_size`` does not evenly divide the per-"
"element quadrature count, the loop runs one extra (shorter) batch on the "
"tail; values larger than ``n_quadrature`` simply collapse to a single "
"full batch."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/user_guide/forms.rst:678 167d7d2235f94e53949da05769954ebf
msgid "Speeding up NodeAssembler with ``compile``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/user_guide/forms.rst:680 4dfa416f1a73469c943af1504ff1188a
msgid ""
":class:`~tensormesh.NodeAssembler` ships a fast path that bypasses "
":func:`torch.vmap` and uses direct broadcast operations instead. Enable "
"it by chaining :meth:`~tensormesh.NodeAssembler.compile`:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/user_guide/forms.rst:701 b5f5d4d6b1784c3592969316bf6e9d01
msgid ""
"The ``mode`` argument additionally controls whether ``torch.compile`` is "
"layered on top: ``\"disable\"`` (default) does the vmap bypass only, "
"``\"default\"`` / ``\"reduce-overhead\"`` / ``\"max-autotune\"`` enable "
"``torch.compile`` with the given level of optimisation. For most users "
"the default ``compile()`` (no ``torch.compile``) is already a large "
"speedup with no warm-up cost. :meth:`~tensormesh.NodeAssembler.flat_mode`"
" is a synonym for ``compile(mode=\"disable\")``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/user_guide/forms.rst:709 9535558d52c2468c87987e18b772cf05
msgid ""
"The fast path only fires when **all three** of the following hold; if any"
" of them fails the call falls back transparently to the vmap path:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/user_guide/forms.rst:712 7e22d7c0188c4678b39fe48b9eb72448
msgid ""
"``.compile()`` has been called on the assembler (``is_compiled`` returns "
"``True``)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/user_guide/forms.rst:714 24b599cc8a9a468c9449dd35da2dcb76
msgid ""
"The mesh has exactly one element type (``len(self.element_types) == 1``)."
" Mixed-element meshes use the vmap path even with compile enabled."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/user_guide/forms.rst:717 ba1a1950a14a492d8287037c431ae774
msgid ""
"No ``func=`` override is passed at call time. Calling "
"``asm(func=alt_form)`` always goes through the vmap path so that you can "
"swap integrands without recompiling."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/user_guide/forms.rst:723 fae2042a768946289891d7f25e69de75
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"The fast path replaces vmap with explicit broadcast operations, which "
"imposes a stricter contract on ``forward``: it must work when ``v`` / "
"``gradv`` arrive with leading ``[n_quadrature, ...]`` / ``[n_element, "
"n_quadrature, ...]`` dimensions rather than as scalars. Closed-form forms"
" that compose those tensors via element-wise ops (``return v``, ``return "
"gradv @ vec``) work as-is; forms that index or reshape per-quadrature "
"inputs may need a few broadcast tweaks, or are simpler to leave on the "
"default vmap path. The fast path also does not auto-supply ``x``; if you "
"need coordinates, pass them in under a custom name (``point_data={\"xy\":"
" mesh.points}`` then ``forward(self, xy, v)``)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/user_guide/forms.rst:737 6e867006ff514b78a4589a86c97e876f
msgid "Writing your own assembler"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/user_guide/forms.rst:739 16c1eec4ddbc4e958ae9c355f3d30590
msgid ""
"The library's design assumes most users will, at some point, write a "
"custom assembler. Here is the practical recipe."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/user_guide/forms.rst:742 fbf90a91b9834411be1b941c4e3a522b
msgid ""
"**1. Pick the base class** by what you're assembling — a matrix "
"(:class:`~tensormesh.ElementAssembler`), a load vector "
"(:class:`~tensormesh.NodeAssembler`), or a boundary term "
"(:class:`~tensormesh.FacetAssembler`). If the integrand is most naturally"
" expressed as a scalar energy density, use the ``.energy()`` path on "
":class:`~tensormesh.ElementAssembler` instead of writing the residual + "
"stiffness by hand — autograd will do that for you."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/user_guide/forms.rst:750 700e9aec0e2343d58d99db213d0ffa63
msgid ""
"**2. Implement ``forward(self, ...)``**. Use only the parameter names "
"listed in :ref:`forms-contract` (``u``, ``v``, ``gradu``, ``gradv``, "
"``x``, ``gradx``), plus any keys you intend to pass through "
"``point_data``, ``element_data``, ``scalar_data``. Return the per-point "
"integrand at the right rank: scalar problems return ``[B, B]`` (Element) "
"or ``[B]`` (Node / Facet); block problems return ``[B, B, H, H]`` or "
"``[B, H]``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/user_guide/forms.rst:758 52b3443e468d4da3bbcffe9b92808f47
msgid ""
"**3. Stash parameters in ``__post_init__``**, not ``__init__``. The base "
"class's ``__init__`` wires up the projector, transformation, and edges; "
"``__post_init__`` runs immediately after with the constructor kwargs and "
"is where ``self.E = E`` belongs."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/user_guide/forms.rst:763 35ba9c7029e346a1b46d97277f80b559
msgid ""
"**4. Build the assembler via** "
":meth:`~tensormesh.ElementAssembler.from_mesh` **and call it.** "
"Constructor kwargs are forwarded to ``__post_init__``. The instance is "
"callable (and is an :class:`torch.nn.Module`, so ``.to(device)`` / "
"``.double()`` Just Work)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/user_guide/forms.rst:768 a32718dd43a949cfb13e1b9de7395fb9
msgid "A self-contained template covering both styles:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/user_guide/forms.rst:792 4884a6afa30a429f9382e198c719dfec
msgid "**Debugging tips**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/user_guide/forms.rst:794 a6eec341c5a948368aa33fcbfb22244b
msgid ""
"If the dispatch fails with ``ValueError: <name> is not supported``, the "
"parameter name doesn't match any built-in or any key you passed in the "
"data dicts. Check for typos like ``grad_u`` vs ``gradu`` or "
"``displacment`` vs ``displacement``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/user_guide/forms.rst:798 634806ea544d468fb273acbaf5db0409
msgid ""
"If you hit a shape error inside ``forward``, set ``batch_size=1`` and "
"call the assembler on a one-element mesh; the tensors handed in are then "
"small enough to ``print`` and reason about. Remember that ``forward`` "
"runs *under vmap* — what you see has the leading element / quadrature "
"dimensions stripped."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/user_guide/forms.rst:803 b6e937fe417e42adbafccc77306ae25b
msgid ""
"For sanity-checking the assembled output, run a known integral: a "
"``MassElementAssembler`` should give ``1^T M 1 == area`` for the unit "
"function; a ``FacetAssembler`` returning ``v`` should sum to the boundary"
" length; a ``LaplaceElementAssembler`` applied to a linear field ``u = "
"x`` should yield zero residual. The ``tests/assemble/test_facet.py`` file"
" has a battery of these closed-form checks."
msgstr ""

